Commentary: OUT! RUN OUT! Would you believe it? Sarfaraz Khan departs on 62, sacrificing his wicket here. This is on a fuller length on off, Ravindra Jadeja steers it to mid on and calls for the single but stops midway. But Sarfaraz Khan is quick to respond and is already halfway outside the crease when Jadeja sends him back and Mark Wood hits the bull's eye at the non-striker's end to remove Sarfaraz Khan. A fantastic innings from the debutant comes to an end in a disappointing way!

Commentary: Jadeja breaches the 100 finally! A sensational innings from the southpaw at his home ground. On the back of a length on the stumps, Ravindra Jadeja tucks it to backward square leg for a single. He gets to the century after a long wait in his nineties. A valuable knock and that sword celebration again comes out but it is fairly muted given the circumstances. India were under extreme pressure after being three down under ten overs, but he made it look easy to bat. A sheer display of patience and composure by him after being promoted on number 4, and he does the job for his team.  A brilliant knock from Jaddu.

Commentary: OUT! LBW! It is that man, Ravindra Jadeja again! He gets the big fish, Joe Root now and the Men in Blue are well and truly on top here. This is a quicker delivery, full and on middle, turns away a bit, Joe Root goes down to sweep it away, but yorks himself and misses to get hit on the pads. The ball lobs up and Rohit Sharma at first slip grabs it as well. There is a huge shout, the umpire gives it out LBW. Root takes the review after discussing it with his skipper. UltraEdge shows a spike but it is of the bat hitting the ground as the replay shows a big gap between bat and ball. Ball Tracking shows two reds and that it is just clipping the off pole. Root just like Crawley is not happy with the decision but will have to walk back. England loses half their side now and still needs 507 runs to win!
